Police in Plateau and Operation Safe Haven, the the multi-security taskforce maintaining peace in the state, have confirmed the killing of three people in Zanwra community in Bassa local government area of Plateau state on Friday night. State Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Tyopev Terna confirmed in a statement that the attack was carried out by unknown gunmen suspected to be herdsmen but was reported on Saturday. Terna gave the names of the victims as "Emmanuel Gado, age 22 years, Ladi Monday, age 30 years and Mary Monday, age 5 years." He said police detectives led by the Divisional Crime Officer (DCO) of Bassa Police Division mobilised to the scene of crime and have since recovered one expended shell of 7.62mm ammunition. On his part,Â  Operation Safe Haven Media and Information Officer, Major Adam Umar while confirming the incident said investigation was in progress to arrest the perpetrators. He said the Commander of the taskforce, Major General Augustine Agundu had visited the scene and paid a condolence visit on the paramount ruler of the Irigwe of Bassa. He urged members of the public to come forward with vital information to assist security agencies in tracking down the perpetrators.